txt.en: You have done much to hinder the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog.\n\nYou should raise a banner of the Haban'akkâ of Thráin at Muru Azog.
Defeated Ufúrzrak Orcs at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Defeat Ufúrzrak thrug-hai at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Orcs, thrug-hai, and banners of the Ufúrzrak clan can be found at Muru Azog.\n\nKing Thráin has commanded you to join in the assault at Muru Azog. You should aid the Haban'akkâ of Thráin.
Defeated Ufúrzrak thrug-hai at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Destroy banners of the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Destroyed banners of the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
The Haban'akkâ of Thráin will be victorious!
Before Nud-mekhem, the old East-gate of Khazad-dûm, Azog's clan, the Ufúrzrak, dwell to defend their would-be realm from the Haban'akkâ of Thráin.
Raise a banner of the Haban'akkâ of Thráin at Muru Azog

'The Haban'akkâ has need of your aid, my friend.

'I have received word that Azog's clan, the Ufúrzrak, still cling to their encampment in the shadow of Nud-mekhem. Neither Azog, nor his sons, nor any of his kin shall ever again find quarter at Khazad-dûm! In Thrór's name, I swear it!

'Let the Ufúrzrak know the wrath of the Haban'akkâ! Death to Azog and all of his kin!'
Defeat Ufúrzrak Orcs at Muru Azog ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
